30/09/2003
MOSCOW, Russia -- During the opening ceremony for the Days of Bulgarian Culture in Russia on Monday (29 September), President Vladimir Putin and his Bulgarian counterpart, Georgi Parvanov, praised the strengthened ties between their countries. 
Putin described Bulgaria as a "brotherly country . 
which we trust" saying that the 10-year decline in relations was virtually over. 
He said the two countries have found new opportunities for co-operation in the fields of energy, science and nuclear research, and tourism. 
Parvanov in turn described the year 2003 as the most fruitful in recent history in terms of dialogue. 
(Trud, 24 Chassa, Dnevnik - 30/09/03; ITAR-TASS, BTA, BNT -29/09/03)
